This is the *unofficial* home page of a little LaTeX class (a spin-off, actually) I wrote years ago as a small contribution to the <a href="http://ctan.org/tex-archive/macros/latex/contrib/calendar/" target="_blank">LaTeX Calendar Bundle.</a> What you can find here is always the latest "snapshot"; the *real, official* release is <a href="http://ctan.org/tex-archive/macros/latex/contrib/calendar/contrib/evweek/" target="_blank">available on CTAN</a> and is probably included in your TeX/LaTeX distribution, so you really don't need to download it: look at your TeX/LaTeX distribution's package manager.

So, why did I put everything on-line? Keep reading...

### Contributing

Embrace the way of Open Source: if you think something is wrong, could be bettered and *you have the skill* to change the World, do it! Contributions are welcome in any form, but I'd rather you follow these steps:

* fork the <a href="https://github.com/baldowl/evweek" target="_blank">project</a> on GitHub;
* work in a topic branch;
* write your additions/bug fixes;
* commit with a clear message;
* send me a pull request for the topic branch.

Happy TeXing!
